<br>
Last night, I debuted a new weapon in my arsenal: a blood point. Now, the monk can taunt off me rarely, but I'd say in 80% of the fights I managed to keep taunt the entire fight, and in the majority of the remaining 20%, I kept taunt for most of the fight before the mob turned on the monk. My weapon combination was a blood point in the primary hand and a lammy in the off-hand (both piercing and 1HS skills are maxed and equal, btw).<br>
<br>
With the lammy in primary and snare whip in off-hand I could not taunt off him worth a damn. Things were a little better with the bloodpoint in primary and snare whip in off-hand, but not by much. I'm sold on the BP primary / lammy secondary combo.<br>
<br>
If you originally asked the question as purely a matter of theory, then you can put a proc'ing weapon in the off-hand, but if you really want to taunt, put it in the primary hand if the weapon ratio supports it.<br>
<br>
Just my observations...if things change radically for me tonight (like, I can't taunt off the monk again), I'll post it here, otherwise, I'm happy with my combo for the time being. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
